		-- CA Health and Safety Code section 1375.9(a) and (c) 
		-- (a) A health care service plan shall ensure there is at least one full-time equivalent primary care physician for every 2,000 enrollees of the plan. The number of enrollees per primary care physician may be increased by up to 1,000 additional enrollees for each full-time equivalent non-physician medical practitioner supervised by that primary care physician. 
		
		-- (d) For purposes of this section,a primary care provider includes a “non-physician medical practitioner,” which is defined as a physician assistant performing services under the supervision of a primary care physician in compliance with Chapter 7.7 (commencing with Section 3500) of Division 2 of the Business and Professions Code or a nurse practitioner performing services in collaboration with a physician pursuant to Chapter 6 (commencing with Section 2700) of Division 2 of the Business and Professions Code. 
		
		-- (e) This section shall remain in effect only until January 1,2019,and as of that date is repealed,unless a later enacted statute,that is enacted before January 1,2019,deletes or extends that date.

-- Example calc:
-- Based ON the above,a PCP with a full time NP and PA could have up to 4000 members.
-- PCP=2000
-- NP= 1000
-- PA= 1000
